Package: NIRApost
Type: Package
Title: Post-Processing Tools for the NodeIdentifyR Algorithm (NIRA)
Version: 1.1.0
Date: 2026-03-21
Authors@R: c(
    person("Fei",      "Wang",  email = "bjnwangfei0501@outlook.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Yiming",   "Wu",    role = "aut"),
    person("Yibo",     "Wu",    role = "aut"),
    person("Tingshao", "Zhu",   role = "aut"))
Description: Provides a three-step validation pipeline for the
    NodeIdentifyR Algorithm (NIRA) in Ising network analysis:
    (1) moderation effect testing as a theoretical prerequisite
    (runMgmmAnalysis), (2) permutation-based significance testing with
    multiple-comparison correction (permutationNIRAtest, plotMeanNIRA),
    and (3) repeated-simulation stability assessment (stabilityNIRAtest,
    findMaxN, plotMaxN). Missing data utilities (checkMissing,
    imputeData) and five real-world datasets are included.
    Backward-compatible aliases preserve all original tutorial-article
    function names.
